# Next.js Form Patterns

- **Form state**: Always use `react-hook-form` to manage form state and submission in React components.
- **Validation schema**: Always use `zod` schemas for validation and type inference instead of ad-hoc validation or hand-written TypeScript types.
- **UI components**: Use shadcn UI form primitives (`Form`, `FormField`, `FormItem`, `FormLabel`, `FormControl`, `FormMessage`) to render fields.
- **Single source of truth**: Validation rules should live in the Zod schema; avoid duplicating them in component props or inline conditionals when possible.
- **Types from schemas**: Infer TypeScript types from Zod (`z.infer<typeof FormSchema>`) instead of redefining interfaces.

## Example Pattern

```tsx
import { z } from "zod";
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";

import { Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage } from "@/components/ui/form";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

const FormSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, "Name is required"),
  email: z.string().email("Enter a valid email"),
});

type FormValues = z.infer<typeof FormSchema>;

export function ExampleForm() {
  const form = useForm<FormValues>({
    resolver: zodResolver(FormSchema),
    defaultValues: {
      name: "",
      email: "",
    },
  });

  function onSubmit(values: FormValues) {
    // Submit logic here, using validated values
  }

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className="space-y-4">
        <FormField
          control={form.control}
          name="name"
          render={({ field }) => (
            <FormItem>
              <FormLabel>Name</FormLabel>
              <FormControl>
                <Input placeholder="Your name" {...field} />
              </FormControl>
              <FormMessage />
            </FormItem>
          )}
        />

        <FormField
          control={form.control}
          name="email"
          render={({ field }) => (
            <FormItem>
              <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>
              <FormControl>
                <Input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" {...field} />
              </FormControl>
              <FormMessage />
            </FormItem>
          )}
        />

        <Button type="submit">Save</Button>
      </form>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

## Non-Preferred Patterns

- Avoid using `useState` for individual form fields instead of `react-hook-form`.
- Avoid manual `onSubmit` validation without Zod schemas.
- Avoid mixing multiple validation libraries in the same project or form; standardize on `zod`.

